reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: Investing to achieve elimination for Malaria and impact against TB and HIV in Cabo Verde

description.narrative: Cabo Verde - Multicomponent - Coordination Committee of the Fight against AIDS of Cabo Verde - CCS-SIDA. This program has the following goals: To reduce new HIV infections by 30% by 2020;. To reduce mortality due to TB by 36% by 2020;. To ensure treatment for 100% of suspected MDR-TB cases;. To maintain the incidence of malaria at less than 1 indigenous case per 1000 inhabitants, and zero deaths per year from malaria in the country by the end of 2020;. The objectives of this program are: To reduce the rate of mother-to-child transmission of HIV to less than 1% by 2020;. To increase condom use rate up to 90% amongst sex workers and men who have sex with men and to 75% amongst drug users, both by 2020;. To increase ART coverage rate to 90% by 2020;. To maintain the lost to follow-up rate for TB cases at 0% by- 2020;. To maintain treatment coverage for diagnosed TB cases at 100% by 2020;. To reduce cases of death amongst TB/HIV co-infected patients to 50% by 2020;. To provide full protection to the population at risk in malaria transmission areas through vector control by 2020;. To maintain a functional epidemiological surveillance system between now and 2020;. To increase the proportion of the population acquainted with methods to prevent and control malaria up to 80% by 2020;. To treat 100% of MDR-TB cases by 2020;
